<br>
  There were voices, echoing ahead in the tunnels. Daon stopped to listen. Two, no, four voices. Beautiful accents. Not human, but Teir'Dal. The Dark Elven language. Even the men of their race had beautiful voices. But many did not notice. Most people who heard them, were their current victims of torture. Their victims never had time to appreciate the dark elves's melodious tones, over the sound of their own screaming. If the victims were lucky, the dark elves who captured them were male. If the victims were male, most of what was done to them was typical, physical torture. The cutting of skin, muscle, and bone. Followed by death, typically. If the victims were female, they were lucky if they were not raped before, or even during the torture. Daon did not approve of rape. Even for a murderer in service to Innoruuk, there were some boundaries that should not be crossed, in Daon's opinion. In that aspect, Daon was perhaps, &quot;almost&quot; similar to the Knights Above. Which is what Daon's family called the Palladins of Marr.<br>
<br>
  Daon quietly moved ahead. His black armor made no sound. The armor was designed so the metal plates did not grind together. His blood red cloak covering him, almost like a shroud, Daon quietly moved up to the scene ahead him.<br>
<br>
  It seemed one of the so called &quot;adventurers&quot; sent to find Daon was captured by the Teir'Dal. The human male was huddled in a corner, grunting like a wounded animal. He wasn't pleading. He had more strength than that. But he had lost the battle to one of the four Teir'Dal who fought him. The adventurer's armor was split open in numerous places. Blood was flowing out of his body like a damaged wine barrel. He had no hands. Most of the blood was spurting from where his opponent had cut his hands off. The adventurer was defiant. Unable to speak from the pain. He still defied the Teir'Dal with his stare. A refusal to die in his eyes, mixed with the mind racking pain. He kept the defiance in his eyes, even as the life left them.<br>
<br>
  One of the Teir'Dal was a woman, who turned to look Daon in the eyes. It seemed as if she knew he was there, but didn't acknowledge him until the adventurer was dead. The Teir'Dal's physical beauty, in general, matched their haunting voices. The women of the Teir'Dal were especially beautiful. This Teir'Dal woman, had a cruel smile on her face. She wore a chain around her neck. Attached to the chain were two hooks. Impaled on the hooks were two, bloody, severed hands.<br>
