 of them. There were even worse things Daon may have &quot;seen&quot;, through his mother's eyes, as an unborn child. Things his mother and her friends did to childr...no. There are things even this storyteller cannot tell. Some stories should not be told. Many people claim to be evil as a way of boosting their self esteem, hoping others fear them. Many people claim to be evil, because they are &quot;naughty&quot; or &quot;angry&quot; or &quot;misunderstood&quot;. Or because they have killed others. Death is a mercy. They don't understand. To them evil is just a title. True evil goes beyond the word and past insanity.<br>
<br>
     Daon is evil. He is not as evil as his mother. He is not a torturer. Although he knows how. His is a killer, in service to a dark god. But there is much more horrible evil in the world than Daon. The knight in armor, screaming at Daon, believes him to be the epitome of all that is evil. If only he knew...<br>
<br>
     &quot;Murderer!&quot; The knight in silver armor screamed . &quot;Five people are dead! Their bodies chopped by YOUR sword and SHRIVELED by your black magic! I saw you in Qeynos that night! I saw what you DID to them! You cut them down without hesitation,and feed on their life force like the monster you are! I was helpless to stop you then, but I have tracked you down to this city and I will stop you now!&quot;  Daon stood there quietly. His Blood red cape covering most of his body. It may have been the darkness of the tunnels, but it seemed Daon was covered in shadows, compared to the Paladin's &quot;light&quot;. His forehead slightly furrowed, as he &quot;politely&quot;, calmly listened to the enraged knight. Daon seemed to be studying him. A question seemed to be forming on his lips, he was just trying to find the &quot;correct&quot; words to say.<br>
&quot;Why...do all you Paladins talk like drunk Bards... in a romance story?&quot; Daon's hand slowly gripped the handle of his bastard sword, beneath the slightly flowing folds of his crimson cape.<br>
