knight take the offensive. Trying to &quot;feel&quot; his opponent's fighting strategy. The knight, taking a step and then twisting his torso into each attack in a rapid pace, growled with each strike against Daon's &quot;persistant&quot; sword. Which Daon managed to bring up in a defensive position each time. Daon's face was grim with determination and his eyes showed an inner fire of hate. Hate, building with each parry. The life of a Shadowknight was one of constant inner conflict. For the Dismal Rage, their hatred was their strength. Hatred gave them the ability to use their dark magic, to it's fullest potential. But this hatred could get in the way of planning and strategy. A potentally lethal flaw, against a more skilled opponent. <br>
<br>
     Daon suddenly noticed, the Paladin wasn't using any of his own magic. He was fighting like a warrior. Pure skill and strength to beat an opponent down. Daon inwardly chastised himself for acting like a similar fool. That was when Daon missed a parry against the Paladin, and the knight's sword cleaved into Daon's left shoulder and into the bone, spraying Daon's face with his own blood. Daon grunted in pain and then Daon's sword arm glowed green with dark magic. The Paladin arched his back and cried out in agony at the ceiling of the tunnels, as his body was poisoned by Daon's necromancy. The Paladin quickly lowered his gaze, his eyes glowing white with his own magic, at the Shadowknight. Daon's world went black with blindness. Before he could react, he felt the Paladin's sword slice thru his armor and into his chest, then his stomach.<br>
<br>
     Elsewhere, on the other side of Antonica. In a forest shelter called Surefall; Myna the half elf stretched on her bed. Enjoying the feel of the morning sunlight on her naked body. She arched her back like a cat, then leaned over to wake her lover. &quot;Don't bother waking him.&quot; Said a man standing in the front of her room, the door closed behind him. &quot;He won't need to help you with what I have in mind.&quot; Myna sat up in the bed, not afraid of the uninvited &quot;guest&quot; in her room. She was angry  that he obviously snuck in. To stare at her body in her sleep, no doubt. She stood up, letting him get a good look at her slender yet volumptious form. &quot;Well this is all you'll ever get. So enjoy the moment.&quot; She said with a dangerous glare in her eyes. &quot;You will walk out that door blinded and castrated before you ever place your hands on THIS body.&quot; She held up her arms as if to show off her body...and the daggers she held in each hand. The &quot;guest&quot; stepped back against the door, holding his hands up in a peaceful gesture. He stuttered for a moment then regained his composure. &quot;I meant a mission! A ...job!&quot; He haden't meant for his words to come out like it sounded when he first spoke. It HAD been on his mind of course. Just looking at her! Clothed or unclothed, gods above! He wanted her! Just one hour...He quickly explained the situation, nervously looking back and forth at Myna's two daggers. His son had become a Paladin and saw what could only had been a Shadowknight, slaughter two young soldiers on duty in the sewers of Qeynos. Then two beggers who got in his way. The Shadowknight then made his way to the surface, thru secret tunnels. He was leaving the area, glancing back towards the front gate guards to make certain he was unseen, when a priest stopped him. After having some unknown conversation with the priest, the Shadowknight suddenly drew his sword and stabbed the priest completely through. Then quickly ran away. When the &quot;guest's&quot; son called for the city Paladins to give chase, they were horrified, but said the Shadowknight was but one of many evils in Qeynos. They must focus on the corrupt guards, to keep the city safe. They helped the young paladin with his training and sent him on a quest to find and stop the Shadowknight. Myna's &quot;guest&quot; wasn't happy with this, since his son was the Paladin sent on the quest. &quot;You're a Ranger!&quot; he said. &quot;You can track down the Shadowknight and kill him before my son finds him! You're skilled! You could kill him!&quot; The &quot;guest's&quot; face was animated by the idea of Myna fulfilling the quest before his son was ever in danger. When he mentioned the amount of money he would give, Myna's eyes lit up with interest.<br>
<br>
     Daon quickly summoned up all the dark power at his command. Concentrating past the pain of each new wound the Paladin gave him, holding in his stomach with his right hand; Daon pulled part of the knight's life force out of him and into Daon himself. His wounds healing with the stolen life essence and still blind, Daon slammed his back against a wall of the tunnel. The Paladin's attacks did not stop, but at least Daon could tell where the next attack would come from. Gritting his teeth against the pain of each new wound, Daon was able to block a few attacks by pure luck. Eyes blinking and hurting, Daon's sight suddenly returned. With a vicious snarl, more animal-like than human, Daon sent a bolt of pure, dark magic at the knight. The Paladin's blood began to boil in side his veins. The Paladin's scream was quickly cut off by Daon's sword, stabbing between his ribs. Daon twisted the blade and two rows of ribs, stretched wide inside the already mangled flesh, cracked. Daon suddenly, savagely pulled the blade out. Steped in and swung his blade low and to the side, slicing open the Paladin's bowls. Entrails dropped to the floor with a sickening splash. The Paladin's body glowed. The knight stood up as his bowels seemed to defy gravity and place themselves back in him. The wound almost completely healed. Daon glared in fustration. Paladins did not die easy.<br>
