     Parrying another blow from the Paladin, sparks flying in his face, Daons arms grew tired. The Paladin was physically stronger and at least equal in skill. Daon's poison magic infected the Paladin and he focused on keeping the blood boiling within his enemy. Despite the agony the knight was obviously in, the Paladin's magic and willpower kept him fighting. Daon knew he wouldn't win. The Paladin slammed his battered shield against Daon's head, stunning him. The knight's chipped sword sliced down and severed Daon's right hand. A roar of pure pain and rage echoed down the Freeport tunnels.<br>
<br>
    Daon grabbed the Paladin by his face and hatred erupted from the Shadowknight in a form of pure power. Red death magic flowed from Daon's hands and dissolved half of the Paladin's face in a crimson mist. The Paladin's scream was garbled from having only part of a mouth. Daon felt drained. The pain from having his hand severed and from all his hatred flowing out into a Harm Touch, left him feeling tired. Physically and well as within. For a moment, just a moment, he felt pity for the knight trying to scream with only half a face. He must have been more tired than he thought. <br>
<br>
   The Paladin's magic began to heal his face. Choking and sobbing in misery and frustration, his own hate and rage building in his eyes, the Paladin advanced. Summoning shadows to entangle the Paladin and slow him down, Daon staggered away from the unrelenting knight. Calling Daon a coward and a fool, the Paladin struggled to catch up. Fighting against the bonds of shadow restraining him. &quot;Come and get me, holy man!&quot; Daon spat.  Gaining enough distance from the Paladin, Daon searched in a pocket of his coat with his remaining hand. He tried to ignore the madding, dizzying pain. Tried to ignore his blood spraying out and the strength going with it. Daon scattered bone chips on the ground. Within seconds, a complete set of bones formed from the fragments. Assembling into an unholy abomination. A skeletal servent that existed only to please it's master. Calling on more of the dark power, Daon enhanced the servents power, and drained more of the Paladin's life force to stop the bleeding of the stump where his hand was. Feeling some strength return but still dizzy from the pain, Daon ran ahead and found a familiar set of stairs. Hearing the sound of the Paladin fighting the undead slave, Daon ran up the stairs and turned around a corner.<br>
      He knew he couldn't hide. He still bled a trail. Easy for anyone to pick up. Daon moved farther down the upstairs tunnel, feet splashing in the sewer water, to an apparent dead end. The tunnel ended with a drop at least twenty feet down to a deep pool of water. The water passing his feet forming a small waterfall into the pit below. He saw something in the water. He remembered the way correctly. Daon began casting a spell.<br>
     The Paladin, shaking off the bonds of shadow and using the last of his magic to heal the poison and agony of his own blood boiling, quickly destroyed the undead slave.  He quickly followed the blood trail up a set of stairs to find Daon at the end of a tunnel. A tunnel that led to nothing but a drop below. Flowing sewer water ran past both their feet and off the end of the tunnel. Magic flowed around the Shadowknight and then...nothing. The Shadowknight was still there. No teleporting through shadows. The Shadowknight, defiance still in his eyes, turned around to face the drop as the Paladin charged, and jumped off.<br>
<br>
     Hearing a loud splash, the Paladin knew then, there was a large pool at the bottom. Anything more shallow, would have resulted in the sound of the Shadowknight's collision echoing thoughout the tunnels.<br>
      Daon was sinking like a man in armor would sink. Barely keeping conscious, he striped the armor off, one piece at a time. Keeping an eye on the shadow he saw earlier. <br>
     The Paladin saw that the Shadowknight wasn't coming up.  He dropped his shield,took off the heavest parts of his armor, and leaped in. Daon had to go up for air. With most of his armor off, he was able to swim to the surface long enough to see the Paladin's splash. Taking a deep breath, Daon dived down. The Paladin was already taking powerful strokes towards Daon, despite the injuries he still suffered. The Paladin's face was reformed, but the skin had not regrown. With that appearance, the Paladin was almost as imposing as the horrors swimming up behind him from the shadows. Pale, shriveled skin. Milk white eyes and lips stretched back to reveal teeth in a horrible grin. Fingertips worn down to the bone, sharpened like claws. Tattered and decayed clothes. The Drowned Men of Freeport. Undead who haunted the deep of the city sewers, quickly swarmed around the Paladin. Bony fingers pierced exposed skin. Yellowed teeth bit and tore at the neck and face. Daon could hear and feel the Paladin's underwater scream as he was pulled back from him. The water quickly turning red. The look of pure horror in the Paladin's eyes, as he reached out a bitten and bloody hand. Fingers had been chewed off. Reaching towards Daon. Not to drag him down but reaching for help. His eyes wide and pleading. Daon felt haunted at that moment. A strange feeling for a Shadowknight. He did not understand it, so he shrugged it off. The Paladin had completely disappeared into the darkness of the red water.<br>
<br>
     Daon swam back up to gain another breath and dived back down to retrieve his armor. The pain of his arm was gone. He felt nothing but a numbness. All over. Everywhere. He was very tired.<br>
      After finding pieces of armor and taking them to a shallow side, bit by bit, Daon only had one piece left to reclaim. It had drifted towards the shadows, where the Drowned Men floated. Daon was unafraid of them. The last spell he cast made him invisible to undead.<br>
